    "## 6. Model 1: Baseline CNN (From Scratch)\n",
    "\n",
    "A custom CNN with 4 convolutional blocks and Global Average Pooling. No pretrained weights.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Architecture rationale (evidence-based):**\n",
    "- **4 blocks, 32\u219264\u2192128\u2192256 filters:** Follows the VGG-style doubling pattern (Simonyan & Zisserman, 2014). Spatial resolution halves at each MaxPool while channel depth doubles \u2014 early layers capture edges/textures, deeper layers capture material-level semantic features.\n",
    "- **Two 3\u00d73 convolutions per block:** Two stacked 3\u00d73 kernels have the same receptive field as one 5\u00d75 but with fewer parameters and more non-linearities (VGG principle).\n",
    "- **BatchNorm after each Conv:** Training stability, allows higher learning rates, mild regularisation (Ioffe & Szegedy, 2015).\n",
    "- **Dropout2d (0.25) per block, Dropout (0.5) in classifier:** Spatial dropout prevents feature map co-adaptation; higher dropout in the dense layers where overfitting risk is greatest.\n",
    "- **Global Average Pooling (GAP) instead of Flatten:** Reduces parameters drastically (256 vs 256\u00d714\u00d714 = 50,176), reducing overfitting. Standard in modern architectures (ResNet, EfficientNet, ConvNeXt).\n",
    "- **Intentionally modest depth:** With ~4,800 images and no pretrained weights, deeper architectures would overfit. Sharma et al. (2018) showed deeper \u2260 always better. The baseline tests whether pure convolutional feature extraction is sufficient \u2014 expected to underperform transfer learning models significantly."
   ]
