    "## 7. Model 2: EfficientNet-B0 \u2014 Mobile Deployment Target\n",
    "\n",
    "**EfficientNet-B0** (Tan & Le, 2019) uses **compound scaling** \u2014 simultaneously scaling depth, width, and resolution via a principled coefficient. This was **not tested in the original RealWaste paper**.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why B0 specifically (not B1, B2, or higher)?**\n",
    "- **Small dataset guard:** RealWaste has ~4,800 images. Larger variants (B3: 12M params, B4: 19M) risk severe overfitting. B0 at 5.3M parameters provides sufficient capacity without overwhelming the data. Rule of thumb: start with B0, scale up only if validation plateaus due to model capacity, not overfitting.\n",
    "- **Mobile deployment target:** B0 uses 224\u00d7224 input and only 0.39B FLOPs \u2014 specifically designed for mobile and edge devices. B1/B2 require 240/260 input resolution, increasing memory and latency on phones.\n",
    "- **Fair comparison with the paper:** B0's ~5.3M params is comparable to MobileNetV2 (~3.4M) tested by Single et al. \u2014 isolating the effect of compound scaling vs ad-hoc design, not just parameter count.\n",
    "- **Transfer learning sweet spot:** The EfficientNet paper showed B0 matches ResNet-50 accuracy (76% vs 77%) with 5x fewer parameters \u2014 excellent transfer learning efficiency.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Architecture key features:**\n",
    "- MBConv blocks (Mobile Inverted Bottleneck) with Squeeze-and-Excitation (SE) attention\n",
    "- Swish/SiLU activation (smoother gradient flow than ReLU)\n",
    "- Compound scaling balances depth, width, and resolution jointly\n",
    "\n",
    "**Training strategy:** Phase 1: freeze backbone \u2192 train classifier head (5 epochs) \u2192 Phase 2: unfreeze all \u2192 fine-tune with 10x lower learning rate."
   ]
