    "\n",
    "Gradient-weighted Class Activation Mapping (Grad-CAM) visualises which regions of the image the model focuses on when making predictions. This reveals whether the model attends to **material texture** (e.g., paper fibres, plastic sheen) or **object shape** (e.g., bottle silhouette)."
